                    <floruit when="0350" srophe:computed-start="0350" source="#bib1280-2">350</floruit>
                    <note xml:lang="en" type="abstract" xml:id="abstract1280-1">Isaiah of Aleppo was a saint said to be the
          last survivor of the disciples of Mar <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/356">Awgin</persName>, and some traditions attribute the composition of the life of Awgin to
          him. Isaiah and his wife never touched, living together in continence. He travelled
          throughout Mesopotamia and converted 3000 Marcionites.</note>
